xediaAtmMIB.name: xediaAtmMIB
xediaAtmMIB.description: This module defines additional objects for management of ATM links in Xedia devices, above and beyond what is defined in the standard ATM mib, and proposed drafts.

xAtmInterfaceConfTable.name: xAtmInterfaceConfTable
xAtmInterfaceConfTable.description: The Xedia ATM Interface Configuration Table contains extensions to the ATM Interface Configuration Table, one entry per ATM interface.

xAtmInterfaceConfEntry.name: xAtmInterfaceConfEntry
xAtmInterfaceConfEntry.description: An entry in the Xedia ATM Interface Configuration Table.

xAtmInterfaceEmptyCells.name: xAtmInterfaceEmptyCells
xAtmInterfaceEmptyCells.description: Specifies the type of cells that the interface sends as a filler when there is no data to send.

xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpTable.name: xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpTable
xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpTable.description: The Xedia ATM Interface DS3 PLCP Table contains extensions to the ATM Interface DS3 PLCP Table, one entry per ATM interface.

xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpEntry.name: xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpEntry
xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpEntry.description: An entry in the Xedia ATM Interface DS3 PLCP Table.

xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpCellAlign.name: xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpCellAlign
xAtmInterfaceDs3PlcpCellAlign.description: Specifies the cell alignment mechanism used by the DS3 framer. In hec(1) mode, the framer determines cell delineation via the HEC alignment method. In this mode, 53-octet cells are expected. In plcp(2) mode, the framer PLCP framing overhead is used which results in 57-octet cells.

xAtmTrafficDescrTable.name: xAtmTrafficDescrTable
xAtmTrafficDescrTable.description: The Xedia ATM Traffic Descriptor Table contains extensions to the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table.

xAtmTrafficDescrEntry.name: xAtmTrafficDescrEntry
xAtmTrafficDescrEntry.description: An entry in the Xedia ATM Traffic Descriptor Table.

xAtmTrafficDescrDescr.name: xAtmTrafficDescrDescr
xAtmTrafficDescrDescr.description: A textual description for the traffic descriptor.

xAtmTrafficDescrQoSClass.name: xAtmTrafficDescrQoSClass
xAtmTrafficDescrQoSClass.description: This object identifies the QoS Class. It is identical to the atmTrafficDescrQoSClass object in the ATM Mgt MIB except that it provides textual enumerations for the values.

xAtmAal5VccTable.name: xAtmAal5VccTable
xAtmAal5VccTable.description: The Xedia ATM AAL5 VCC Table contains extensions to the ATM AAL5 VCC Performance Parameters, one entry per ATM AAL5 virtual channel on an ATM interface.

xAtmAal5VccEntry.name: xAtmAal5VccEntry
xAtmAal5VccEntry.description: An entry in the Xedia ATM AAL5 VCC Table.

xAtmAal5VccTxPdus.name: xAtmAal5VccTxPdus
xAtmAal5VccTxPdus.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs successfully passed to the ATM interface's driver for transmission on the virtual channel.

xAtmAal5VccTxOctets.name: xAtmAal5VccTxOctets
xAtmAal5VccTxOctets.description: The number of AAL5 octets successfully passed to the ATM interface's driver for transmission on the virtual channel.

xAtmAal5VccTxPduFailures.name: xAtmAal5VccTxPduFailures
xAtmAal5VccTxPduFailures.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs which could not be passed to the ATM interface's driver for transmission on the virtual channel. Possible reasons include VCL operational status down or driver unable to accept PDU due to state or lack of resources.

xAtmAal5VccRxPdus.name: xAtmAal5VccRxPdus
xAtmAal5VccRxPdus.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs successfully received on the virtual channel from the ATM interface and delivered to a higher layer.

xAtmAal5VccRxOctets.name: xAtmAal5VccRxOctets
xAtmAal5VccRxOctets.description: The number of AAL5 octets successfully received on the virtual channel from the ATM interface and delivered to a higher layer.

xAtmAal5VccRxPduDiscards.name: xAtmAal5VccRxPduDiscards
xAtmAal5VccRxPduDiscards.description: The number of AAL5 PDUs received and discarded on the virtual channel from the ATM interface. Possible reasons for discard include: VCL operational state down, no higher layer client connected to VCL, etc.

xAtmCompliance.name: xAtmCompliance
xAtmCompliance.description: The compliance statement for all agents that support this MIB. A compliant agent implements all objects defined in this MIB.

xAtmAllGroup.name: xAtmAllGroup
xAtmAllGroup.description: The set of all accessible objects in this MIB.
